Class StyledDocumentPrinter.Worker

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Thread

  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.awt.print.Printable, java.lang.Runnable, javax.print.event.PrintJobListener
    Enclosing class:
    StyledDocumentPrinter

    private class StyledDocumentPrinter.Worker
extends java.lang.Thread
implements java.awt.print.Printable, javax.print.event.PrintJobListener
    Underlying printing class.

    The print action is implemented by a private internal class to use a devoted thread for the printing and to hide the Printable and PrintJobListener implemented interfaces.

      • analyzeLines

        private int analyzeLines(javax.swing.text.Element element,
               int startLine,
               java.lang.String eol)
                  throws javax.swing.text.BadLocationException
        Gather height informations from all styles.

        Recursively analyze all document to identify the lines and the maximal ascent and height encountered along these lines

        Parameters:
        element - styled element to analyze
        startLine - offset of the start of the current line
        eol - end of line marker
        Returns:
        start of the last line still under analysis
        Throws:
        javax.swing.text.BadLocationException - if some position is wrong

      • identifyEndOfLineMarker

        private java.lang.String identifyEndOfLineMarker(java.lang.String text)
        Identify the end of line marker.

        The end of line marker depends from the operating system that created the text file beeing parsed. It is \n for UNIX, \r for MAC and \n\r for DOS/Windows.

        Parameters:
        text - sample text on which end of line marker will be guessed
        Returns:
        the guessed end of line marker
